hopobject.body: I've got a part-time job alapharma.com Lorcan spoke “very well, very early” but clammed up in front of strangers as a toddler. He was also a bad sleeper. But it was only when he started nursery that the Dillons realised there was a problem. On his first day, he refused to take his hat and coat off and didn’t say a word. “At first, we thought he was just taking longer to settle than other children. But it went on. And on,” says Jayne.
